ls, pink balls and green balls only.\nThe ratio yellow balls : pink balls : green balls = 7 : 3 : 5.\nThere are 42 yellow balls in the bag.\nWork out the total number of balls in the bag.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"calculate"},{"id":"0580-2020MayJune-Paper13-Q13","paper":"2020MayJune-Paper13","qnum":13,"marks":2,"topics":["Probability"],"s":"8.3","d":1,"cat":"probability","topic":"Combined events","qtype":"combined events","g":"mixed","src":"0580/13/M/J/20 Q13","year":2020,"session":"MayJune","tex":"On any day, the probability that Marcus will get a seat on the school bus is 0.93 .\n\n(a) Write down the probability that he will not get a seat on the school bus today.\n\n(b) There are 200 school days in a year.\nWork out the expected number of days in a year that Marcus will not get a seat.","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":1},{"label":"(b)","marks":1}],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"calculate"},{"id":"0580-2020MayJune-Paper13-Q14","paper":"2020MayJune-Paper13","qnum":14,"marks":3,"topics":["Algebra and graphs"],"s":"2.2","d":1,"cat":"algebra","topic":"Algebraic manipulation","qtype":"algebraic manipulation","g":"mixed","src":"0580/13/M/J/20 Q14","year":2020,"session":"MayJune","tex":"Simplify.\n\n(a) $p^{2} \\times p^{4}$\n\n(b) $m^{15} \\div m^{5}$\n\n(c) $(k^{3})^{5}$","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":1},{"label":"(b)","marks":1},{"label":"(c)","marks":1}],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"recall","cmd":"simplify"},{"id":"0580-2020MayJune-Paper13-Q15","paper":"2020MayJune-Paper13","qnum":15,"marks":3,"topics":["Transformations and vectors"],"s":"7.1","d":1,"cat":"vectors","topic":"Transformations","qtype":"transformations","g":"mixed","src":"0580/13/M/J/20 Q15","year":2020,"session":"MayJune","tex":"Describe fully the single transformation that maps shape A onto shape B.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"recall","cmd":"describe"},{"id":"0580-2020MayJune-Paper13-Q16","paper":"2020MayJune-Paper13","qnum":16,"marks":3,"