 value of\n\n\\[\\dfrac{71 \\times 32.4}{4.8 \\times 2}\\]\n\nYou must show all your working.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"recall","cmd":"calculate"},{"id":"0580-2020MayJune-Paper13-Q20","paper":"2020MayJune-Paper13","qnum":20,"marks":4,"topics":["Number"],"s":"1.6","d":1,"cat":"number","topic":"The four operations","qtype":"four operations","g":"mixed","src":"0580/13/M/J/20 Q20","year":2020,"session":"MayJune","tex":"Des thinks of two numbers.\nThe sum of his two numbers is -6.\nThe difference between his two numbers is 62.\nFind the two numbers.\n\n and","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"find"},{"id":"0580-2020MayJune-Paper13-Q21","paper":"2020MayJune-Paper13","qnum":21,"marks":4,"topics":["Mensuration"],"s":"5.4","d":1,"cat":"mensuration","topic":"Surface area and volume","qtype":"surface area and volume","g":"mixed","src":"0580/13/M/J/20 Q21","year":2020,"session":"MayJune","tex":"A solid cylinder has radius 3 cm and height 4.5 cm.\nCalculate the total surface area of the cylinder.\n\n cm$^2$","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"calculate"}]